I guess before I moved here this was the place for live music.
Every time I talked to friends in Arizona, they were talking about their night at the Goat.
I finally moved out here and got to experience it first hand.
I was not impressed.
First off, the stage and sound is horrible.
It's small and the way the speakers and stage is crafted you don't hear everything.
If you want to hear a particular instrument, you have to move around.
The owner of the bar is a staple in live music in Tempe.
He's been around for a long time.
I feel that this place changed him.
The drinks are overpriced and the food is terrible.
I went once with my obvious pregnant wife and she ordered a coke.
It was small, loaded with ice and $2.50.
She drank it in one sip.
She went up to get a refill and it was another $2.50.
How can you charge $2.50 per sip of coke and charge $10 at the door?
One night I made the mistake of putting my tab on my credit card.
There was $30 worth of drinks on there that I didn't order.
I tried arguing with them and they didn't care.
I was floored.
The only time I will show up at this venue / restaurant again is if there is a band playing that I HAVE to see.
Thank God the Sail Inn is open again.
They treat their customers right, and they are grateful we show up.

