I am somewhat biased in my opinion of Goat Head.
I really LOVE rock music and this place has a kick ass sound system, light show, and stage!
I saw one of my favorite local bands, One Body Too Many, perform here and fell in love.
Now that there is karaoke here on Tuesday nights, it really has become my favorite karaoke spot.
The karaoke is run through the sound system with the light system going.
When you are on the stage, your option, it really feels like you are in concert.
Kind of a good thing but maybe not for some, there is not a huge crowd so your chances to sing lots of songs are relatively good,  Not being a drinker, I have heard some of my friends say that the drinks are over priced and there aren't many good drink specials.
The bartenders have changed frequently, so the kitchen is rarely open, as the owner is oftentimes the bartender of the night.
All in all despite some of the drawbacks- the food, strange people, etc., I still have a really good time.

